	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You want to know why the wiki's submappers definition differ from kevtris's?<br /><br />Because I read his reference and decided it was patently unusable. They were underdescribed (Mindseeker + mapper 80), overfine (VRC4?), apply to non-existant things (see next Â¶), and their release coincided with a time when he was taking a break from the forum.<br /><br />The bonus fictitious mapper 78 variant? Doesn't exist. MMC3 TEROM/TFROM hardwired mirroring? Never used. The mapper 1 weirdness? His original draft was lousy with typoes. Mapper 32? Incomplete. The mapper 34 weirdness? On him.<br /><br />It was necessary to throw the whole thing out and start with just a list of where things were needed. It <strong>contains more mistakes than useful starting points</strong>.<br /><br />There are myriad documented games that rely on the presence/absence of bus conflicts on discrete logic mappers. You can search the wiki for them. <br /><br />So, let's talk specifically about StarTropics. <br />1- There is no definition of MMC6 that makes sense with a PRG-RAM quantity other than 1 KiB.<br />1b- There is no definition of SUROM vs SNROM that makes sense without the latter having 512 KiB PRG-ROM; there is no definition of SNROM, SOROM, and SXROM that makes sense without those three having 8, 16, and 32 KiB of PRG-RAM.<br />2- The decision was made to allocate a field to specify the amount of PRG-RAM AS WELL AS a generic submapper field<br />3- Why specify the same exact information twice in the header (&quot;This is StarTropics ... oh, and just in case you weren't paying attention, this is StarTropics&quot;)<br />3b- Why specify the same exact information twice in the header (&quot;This is Titanic 1912 ... oh, and just in case you weren't paying attention, this is Titanic 1912&quot;)<br />3c- I'd repeat myself for all the S?ROM games, but ugh.<br /><br /><br />Finally, despite your complaint: The reason the NES 2.0 submappers haven't been deployed is EXCLUSIVELY because there isn't a ROM set that uses them. That's it. Nothing less, nothing more.<br /><br />Anyway, Nintendulator already uses PRG RAM size to determine MMC1 behavior and the presence of RAM presence to handle Low G Man. And MESS implements everything as on the wiki ... except for MMC3, because I didn't decide on anything (other than that kevtris's recommendations were inadeuate) until after etabeta implemented things.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


